      "writtenOn": "2017-08-03T17:23:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yep 3 different places.\n2. because the files need to be prefixed differently so that blacklists/ignores can be created around them as mentioned in https://bugs.chromium.org/p/skia/issues/detail?id\u003d6918\u0026desc\u003d2\n3. because we do not have URLs to get those 2 SVGs from so they have been stored directly in GS. Seems like a good way to handle either private SVGs or SVGs handed to us (not from URLs).",
